The paper deals with manipulation problems in voting, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of partial information and the complexity analysis suggest that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of voting rules and their properties is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA), which further supports these categories as likely choices.
